Privacy
Plotaverse – Privacy Policy
Effective Date:
January 1st, 2025
1. Introduction
Welcome to Plotaverse, an AI-powered social platform for creators. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, store, and protect your personal information. By using Plotaverse, you consent to the practices described in this policy.
2. Information We Collect
We collect the following types of information:
Personal Information
: Name, email, username, profile picture, and payment details if applicable.
Usage Data
: Interactions with the platform, content uploads, messages, and user preferences.
AI-Generated Content Data
: Information related to AI-assisted creations and modifications.
Device and Technical Data
: IP address, browser type, device information, and cookies.
3. How We Use Your Information
Your information is used for the following purposes:
To provide and improve our services.
To personalize user experience and content recommendations.
To process transactions and payments.
To ensure platform security and prevent fraud.
To comply with legal obligations.
4. AI Data Processing
AI-generated content may be analyzed to improve platform capabilities.
User data is not sold to third parties but may be used to enhance AI features.
5. Sharing of Information
We may share your information with:
Service Providers
: Payment processors, hosting providers, and analytics services.
Legal Authorities
: When required to comply with the law or protect our rights.
Other Users
: If you choose to share your content publicly.
6. Data Security
We implement reasonable security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. However, no method of transmission is 100% secure.
7. User Rights and Choices
You can access, modify, or delete your personal information through your account settings.
You can request data deletion by contacting info@plotaverse.com.
You may opt out of certain data processing activities where applicable.
8. Retention of Data
Your data is retained as long as necessary to fulfill our services, legal obligations, or resolve disputes.
9. Third-Party Links and Services
Plotaverse may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for their privacy practices, and users should review their policies separately.
10. Children’s Privacy
Plotaverse is not intended for children under 17. If we discover a child’s data has been collected without parental consent, we will delete it.
11. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy at any time. Continued use of Plotaverse after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.
12. Contact Information
For any questions regarding this policy, please contact us at info@plotaverse.com
